  <span id="freeText7580535348351532077" style="display:none">Ray Atlee and his brother are called by their ailing father to his home,as he wants to settle his estate.But when they get there,their father dies,and three million dollars are found in his house.The money is not mentioned in the will.Ray now has to find out where all this cash came from.There is also the additional problem of what to do with it.<br />I'm very fond of this book,as it made me rediscover John Grisham.Years earlier,I read the Pelican Brief,and found it disappointing.When I picked up The Summons,I had very low expectations.But the book surprised me,it was a real page turner.Very suspenseful,and very hard to put down.It made me a Grisham fan.Only the ending is not as good as the rest of the book,otherwise this would have earned five stars.</span>
